// Held-out routing eval (Italian) for the FunctionGemma promotion gate.
// NONE = the router must abstain (general knowledge → assistant). These
// utterances are deliberately NOT in the Italian training data — fresh
// entities and phrasings — so a pass means the model GENERALISED, not
// memorised. Checked against all three Italian training sources: the
// built-in *_EXAMPLES_IT consts, the SKILL.it.md examples, and
// generate-dataset.py's Italian negative pool.
// Positives are canonical Italian skill requests a competent router must
// still route — differently phrased, not tricks.
// The NONE cases carry no live Italian skill trigger (same poisoned-sample
// rule the negative pool follows), so none of them is an utterance a
// keyword skill should have owned.
// Note: "search" is keyword-only (router_eligible=false), so it is never a
// positive target here.
